  <h1 class="post-title">ClearNight Retro</h1>
  <time datetime="2018-05-08">May 8, 2018</time>

  <div class="post-main">
    <div class="blog-body">
      <p><img alt="ClearNight Retro" src="../assets/images/retro-title.png"/></p>

      <p>After a bit of work, I&#39;m proud to introduce <a href="https://atom.io/packages/clearnight-retro-ui">ClearNight Retro</a>, a new dark, relaxed retro theme for Atom! The set is a UI theme with matching syntax theme, but both can work separately with other dark themes like Atom&#39;s own One Dark.</p>

      <p>The core of the theme is forked from <a href="https://github.com/ClearNight/clear-night-ui">Clear Night</a>, and makes use of a relaxed, almost faded color scheme inspired by <a href="https://github.com/morhetz/gruvbox">Gruvbox</a>. The theme set will continue to be maintained by me and the <a href="https://github.com/clearnight">ClearNight organization</a>. I'm no longer using Atom much, I've been leaning more into my <a href="https://github.com/thornjad/aero">configuration of Emacs</a> recently, but the ClearNight themese will continue to receive full support for at least a few years.</p>

      <h2>Take a look</h2>

